2 HOUSE BILL 1498
1 This title applies only in Wicomico County.
2 32–901.
3 (a) IN THIS SECTION, “RETAIL FLOOR SPACE” MEANS THE AREA OF AN
4 ESTABLISHMENT WHERE ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES AND OTHER ITEMS ARE
5 DISPLAYED FOR SALE AND SOLD.
6 (B) There is a Class A beer, wine, and liquor license.
7 [(b)] (C) (1) (I) [A] BEFORE JULY 1, 2026, A license may be issued only
8 to an establishment that has been:
9 [(i)] 1. issued a Class B license; and
10 [(ii)] 2. continually operating as a restaurant in the county since
11 at least 3 months before the application for the license.
12 (II) ON OR AFTER JULY 1, 2026, A LICENSE:
13 1. MAY NOT BE ISSUED TO AN ESTABLISHMENT THAT HAS
14 BEEN ISSUED A CLASS B LICENSE; AND
15 2. MAY BE RENEWED FOR AN ESTABLISHMENT THAT HAS
16 A CLASS B LICENSE THAT WAS ISSUED BEFORE JULY 1, 2026.
17 (2) The Board may not issue a license to an establishment that is a
18 corporation or limited liability company unless the license applicant owns 75% of the total
19 issued capital stock of the corporation or the limited liability company.
20 (3) The Board may issue:
21 (I) NOT MORE THAN ONE LICENSE IN A COUNCILMANIC
22 DISTRICT; AND
23 (II) not more than A TOTAL OF three licenses in the county.
24 (4) THE BOARD MAY NOT ISSUE A LICENSE TO AN ESTABLISHMENT
25 WITH RETAIL FLOOR SPACE OF MORE THAN 3,500 SQUARE FEET.
26 [(c)] (D) (1) Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, the license authorizes
27 the license holder to sell beer, wine, and liquor, at retail at the place described in the
28 application, for off–premises consumption.

