1 (2) [The] FOR A LICENSE ISSUED TO A CLASS B LICENSE HOLDER
2 BEFORE JULY 1, 2026, THE place described in the application:
3 (i) may not exceed 20% of the area normally used in the operation
4 of the restaurant business; and
5 (ii) shall be contiguous to and adjoin the restaurant establishment.
6 [(d)] (E) The license may not be issued for a drugstore unless the applicant:
7 (1) has been doing business at the location applied for in the license for at
8 least 1 year before the date of the application for the license;
9 (2) is the assignee of a business established for at least 1 year before the
10 date of the application for the license at the location applied for; or
11 (3) has been engaged in the retail drug business for at least 3 years.
12 [(e)] (F) (1) The license holder shall purchase liquor for retail sale from a
13 county dispensary or from a wholesaler.
14 (2) A dispensary may not charge the license holder more than 15% above
15 the wholesale operating cost to the dispensary.
16 [(f)] (G) The annual license fee is $4,400 and is in addition to [the] ANY fee
17 THAT MAY BE paid for [the] A Class B license.
18 32–1502.
